WHO   — NINTENDO GAME & WATCH — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Before the Game Boy there was Game & Watch: Gunpei Yokoi's line of single-game LCD handhelds, each a calculator-grade 4-bit chip driving a fixed, pre-printed segment screen. They funded Nintendo's rise, debuted the cross-shaped D-pad, and their dual-screen models prefigured the DS.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
